    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 30 with a high-ceiling core, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (87.42) and **Trea Turner** (72.20). **Yordan Alvarez** is our clear standout, benefiting from a massive 16% park adjustment and a prime spot in the two-hole against Young, whose 4.67 xERA offers the most favorable matchup of the day. Similarly, **Trea Turner** remains an essential start despite the -2% dynamic platoon penalty; his ability to chase stolen bases\u2014our scarcest category\u2014combined with an elite 11% SP skill advantage against Houser makes him a cornerstone of today's 5x5 effort. **Kyle Schwarber** (70.37) rounds out the top-tier plays, leveraging an elite .402 xwOBA to overcome the same platoon headwinds facing **Trea Turner**.\n\nWhile **Colt Keith** (63.34) and **Kazuma Okamoto** (60.36) project as solid starts in the 60-point range, the lineup construction saw a difficult exclusion at the UTIL spot. **Carson Benge** (56.03) narrowly earned the nod, but **Jerar Encarnacion** (39.39) pushed hard for consideration. Ultimately, the algorithm benched **Jerar Encarnacion** because the matchup against S\u00e1nchez, C (3.02 xERA) triggered a significant -19% SP skill penalty, pushing him below our internal 40.0 floor. We continue to monitor the status of **Junior Caminero**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, **Christian Yelich**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Gary Sanchez**, **Luke Raley**, **Josh Smith**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena** as they remain sidelined today due to off-days or roster rotations. Managers should monitor the weather in Houser\u2019s start for any late-breaking precipitation that could dampen the efficiency of **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber**.",
